begin
reserve X for non empty TopSpace;
reserve Y for non empty TopSpace;
theorem
(for f being (Function of X,Y) holds (for X1,X2 being non empty (SubSpace of X) holds (X = ( X1 union X2 ) implies (for x being (Point of X) holds (for x1 being (Point of X1) holds (for x2 being (Point of X2) holds ((x = x1 & x = x2) implies (f is_continuous_at x iff (( f | X1 ) is_continuous_at x1 & ( f | X2 ) is_continuous_at x2)))))))))
proof
let f being (Function of X,Y);
let X1 being non empty (SubSpace of X),X2 being non empty (SubSpace of X);
assume that
A1: X = ( X1 union X2 );
let x being (Point of X);
let x1 being (Point of X1);
let x2 being (Point of X2);
assume that
A2: x = x1
and
A3: x = x2;
thus (f is_continuous_at x implies (( f | X1 ) is_continuous_at x1 & ( f | X2 ) is_continuous_at x2)) by A2,A3,CKB65:1;
thus ((( f | X1 ) is_continuous_at x1 & ( f | X2 ) is_continuous_at x2) implies f is_continuous_at x)
proof
assume that
A4: ( f | X1 ) is_continuous_at x1
and
A5: ( f | X2 ) is_continuous_at x2;
(for G being (a_neighborhood of ( f . x )) holds (ex H being (a_neighborhood of x) st ( f .: H ) c= G))
proof
let G being (a_neighborhood of ( f . x ));
( f . x ) = ( ( f | X1 ) . x1 ) by A2,FUNCT_1:49;
then consider H1 being (a_neighborhood of x1) such that A6: ( ( f | X1 ) .: H1 ) c= G by A4,CKB44:def 1;
(the carrier of X1) c= (the carrier of X) by BORSUK_1:1;
then reconsider S1 = H1 as (Subset of X) by XBOOLE_1:1;
( f . x ) = ( ( f | X2 ) . x2 ) by A3,FUNCT_1:49;
then consider H2 being (a_neighborhood of x2) such that A7: ( ( f | X2 ) .: H2 ) c= G by A5,CKB44:def 1;
(the carrier of X2) c= (the carrier of X) by BORSUK_1:1;
then reconsider S2 = H2 as (Subset of X) by XBOOLE_1:1;
( f .: S2 ) c= G by A7,FUNCT_2:97;
then A8: S2 c= ( f " G ) by FUNCT_2:95;
consider H being (a_neighborhood of x) such that A9: H c= ( H1 \/ H2 ) by A1,A2,A3,CKB18:1;
take H;
( f .: S1 ) c= G by A6,FUNCT_2:97;
then S1 c= ( f " G ) by FUNCT_2:95;
then ( S1 \/ S2 ) c= ( f " G ) by A8,XBOOLE_1:8;
then H c= ( f " G ) by A9,XBOOLE_1:1;
hence thesis by FUNCT_2:95;
end;
hence thesis by CKB44:def 1;
end;

